Released version 0.1.0 · jrosco/vscode-git-notes · GitHub

<a href="https://github.com/jrosco/vscode-git-notes/compare/0.0.1...0.1.0">Changelog</a>

Added
    ❇️ Develop interactive HTML buttons that utilize JavaScript to send messages to a Visual Studio Code function. Upon receiving the messages, the corresponding extension.[code] will be executed. <a href="https://github.com/jrosco/vscode-git-notes/pull/12">#12</a>
    ❇️ Add confirmation message for note removal and pruning git repos <a href="https://github.com/jrosco/vscode-git-notes/pull/15">#15</a>
    ❇️ Webview can now refresh on updates e.g removing a note message <a href="https://github.com/jrosco/vscode-git-notes/pull/14">#14</a>
Fixed
    🐛 When user hit ESC from InputBox when running extension.addGitNoteMessage the command tries to add a message/note instead of cancelling input <a href="https://github.com/jrosco/vscode-git-notes/pull/11">#11</a>
Changed
    🍻 Webview date arrangement / sorting <a href="https://github.com/jrosco/vscode-git-notes/pull/9">#9</a>
